<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">
    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Using Menus" />
    <p><code>ui:menu</code> is a menu component that contains list items. It can be wired to actions
    in a client-side controller and can contain menu items that are retrieved from a model. 
   </p>
    <p><code>ui:menu</code> is nested in <code>ui:dropdown</code> and can contain these list item components:
    <code>ui:actionMenuItem</code>, <code>ui:checkboxMenuItem</code>, <code>ui:radioMenuItem</code>, and a separator component <code>ui:menuItemSeparator</code>.
    </p>
	<auradocs:info>See the <auradocs:defLink descriptor ="ui:menu">ui:menu</auradocs:defLink> component reference.</auradocs:info>
	
	<p>The following demo shows how to use the list item components, which trigger an action on a client-side controller.
	 The dropdown menu and its menu items are hidden by default and shown only when the <code>ui:menuTriggerLink</code> component is clicked, but can be changed by updating the <code>visible</code> attribute on the <code>ui:menu</code> component.</p>
    <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:demoMenu" />
    
    <p>The following demo shows how to use <code>ui:menu</code> to display menu items from a model and retrieve the selected items via the <code>menuItems</code> attribute.</p>
    <auradocs:example descriptor="auradocs:demoMenuMeta" />
    
